 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zacatac>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1674<br> <font color=#333333>(1/25/03 5:06:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1152.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Thurgadin Shawl quest - continued</span><hr size=1> I can give you some info, but never tried to solo there.  Pretty difficult to do. . .<br>
<br>
Best thing is to be up on the WW side of the zone (wiz/druid succor takes you there).  Fight your way through the large mammels that are in the area and clear the way to the pool.  Those big guys are the ones who can drop the Hide you need.<br>
<br>
Once to the pool, the swordfish tooth you need is in there.  You'll need to fight in the pool, fish can't come up on the land. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Now the really fun part.  That pond connects to a well which drops down and leads you to a room FULL of sirens.  These are the ones you need to kill for the seashell with 1 charge EB.  Sometimes mobs can see-invis in the tunnel down, so have to be careful about this.  Go down, head south a short ways, then come up out of the water and into the room.<br>
<br>
Like I said, never tried it soloing.  Those sirens are all enchanters, so get your MR up high.  And I'd use 61 Air pet for stuns if you have it.<br>
