<br>
Swordfish - There is a single pullable one in the pool near the &quot;well&quot; by the WW zone. You'll need to fight in the water (since the mob is waterbound). It drops the Swordfish tooth nearly every time. The technique I used was Epic and some heals mixed in with nukes. You can easily substitute the Epic with the 62 pet depending on availability.<br>
<br>
Molkor Hide - Set up in the tunnel coming out from the WW zone. You can usually find Molkor's up near that &quot;well&quot; area. Single pullable at 60, and drops fairly easily.<br>
<br>
Uthork Tusk - Go to EW...coming from GD, head NE of the giant fort. Those drop the tusk as well, so no need to kill the ones in SG.<br>
<br>
Runes Sea Shell (with 1 charge of EB) - There are 3 places with guarenteed Siren spawns. 1) Bottom of the well. 2) Inside the castle 3) Drop off from wooden bridge at CS zone. All three are extremely dangerous camps that are best avoided. Save up for the 1.1k. It's definitely worth it imo. If you still feel compelled to farm it, I suggest the well camp. Grab an EB item and dive in. If you're lucky, there will be a mix of aquatic and hybrid creatures. The purely aquatic ones will not chase you out of the well, so you can pull the hybrid ones to the surface and slowly make your way down. The safest place is at the bottom of the well, where there are 3 spawns. However, even at level 65, the Sirens are by no means easy.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps.<br>
