<br>
I called this &quot;Pet Stun Pull&quot;.<br>
<br>
You need 61 air pet preferably, but works with epic and 59 air too, you will just need to heal a lot.<br>
<br>
Never forget the spawn timer is 28 minutes in SG, so time the death of the entrance spawn as you do not want having him as an add when you are fighting the pulled &quot;side-ledge&quot; mobs.<br>
<br>
After you have killed by traditional means the entrance mob, you can kill by the same traditional means the lonely seahorse. Than comes the innovative pull technique :<br>
<br>
You see two mobs wandering on each side ledge. When you face the waterfall, the mob on the right ledge is very easy to &quot;Pet Stun Pull&quot;. Just put your air pet (again you need a stunner pet) on follow mode, tell it to attack -do not forget to have see inv on as it will drop invisibility only when engaging the mob- and pet will rush to the ledge.<br>
<br>
As soon you see the mob stunned (it is very easy to see despite you are too far for the spell messages, mob just stands doing nothing), spam your /pet back off key. Works of course even better if you have /pet hold, though I don't know if /pet hold works at that range.<br>
<br>
Your pet will have no trouble to back off with stun (just start spamming the back off key when you see mob has been stunned) and will come back to you, followed by the angry mob. Position it well in the entrance and kill - and only pet has aggro from pull, not you :-)<br>
<br>
For the other mob on the left ledge, things are a bit more tricky because of the pathing, pet has more trouble to reach the mob. But it still works if you wait the mob approaches the end of the ledge (you will see that the mob changes his position from time to time), so just wait it is right at the end of the ledge, than it works, and pet rushes towards it. Same method, rinse repeat.<br>
<br>
At level 61, seahorses always blue, ulthork/bulthar/molkor mostly blue - was able to hold all 4 spawns within the 28 minutes timer without C3. AT level 62, only the seahorse remains blue though. This camp of course is not an xp camp, it is more loot oriented (Velious quets gems, Netted Kelp, Molkor Hide for 7th Shawl, and sometimes you get the Servant Swordfish add which drops a no drop component required also for 7th shawl).<br>
<br>
Your pet will soemtimes, on its way back, be aggroed by a seahorse risponding to the call of help of the pulled mob, but I never had a problem in succeeding the back off command, and pet always came back to me. Seahorses or Servant Swordfish cannot climb out of the water, so you are sure to get the &quot;side-ledge-mob&quot; single.<br>
<br>
A couple of times, a friendly chanter on his way with a group to WW C3ed me, and than I could even take out as a bonus, the two seahorses guarding the cave which leads to the pool area. These cannot be singled, just chain pets on them, you are perfectly safe, they cannot climb out of the water (you cannot cast on them if you are not in the water, but you can send a pet). Mana and Malachite intensive, but fun ... and the seahorses are a bit better xps than the other mobs, though bad loot.<br>
<br>
Enjoy the new Pet Stun Pull Technique - and maybe there are other areas where this could be useful :-)<br>
